(24, 1, '2014-12-05 00:18:17', '2014-12-05 00:18:17', '<span style="font-family: Arial;"><b>Tuesday, September 9</b></span>\r\n\r\n<strong>For those interested in our new tournament teams, winter training, and early-season tournaments for 2015, please read the following carefully. There are some changes from VLL Tournament Teams of past seasons. Please submit <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1_Vn_R7f7JsXTf00l-zsy_QSSCB3s3heY2CNvzCH-k3U/viewform?usp=send_form" rel="nofollow">self-nomination forms</a> no later than <span style="text-decoration: underline;">11:59pm Friday, September 12</span>.</strong>\r\n\r\nFall tryouts will be held <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Sunday, September 14</span> for 10U through 14U players. See time slot details below. A second opportunity will be offered the evening of Wednesday, September 17 for those who are unable to make the primary assessment on Sunday. Exact time slots for that evening will be announced later, based on numbers.\r\n\r\nAs noted in the previous e-mail, participation in these off-season activities and early-spring tournaments is not required in order to play on a VLL Tournament Team in the summer of 2015. However, we hope to leverage our VLL resources and growing enthusiasm for competitive baseball to offer new opportunities to our players. Additional tryouts will be held sometime in May.\r\n<div align="center"><span style="color: #ff6600; font-size: medium;"><strong>Verona Baseball Tournament Teams</strong></span></div>\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Objective:</strong></span> To offer a more competitive option for players with advanced skill and commitment levels.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Expectations:</strong></span> Sportsmanship, commitment, and communication are expected from players and parents of Verona Baseball Tournament Teams (VBTT). With an increased level of competition, an increased level of commitment is also expected. Each team will have designated team practices and tournaments; the number of each will be determined by the coaches of each team.\r\n\r\nAttendance at practices and games is vital and will play a factor in playing time and positions played. Players selected to a VBTT agree to prioritize VBTT practices and games over other sports and minimize conflicts with VBTT practices and games. Communication with coaches is essential when practices or games will be missed. Please let your coach know of any planned vacations or other conflicts that will prevent attendance of practices and games. Ability to commit may play a role in VBTT selection. It is not the intention for a VBTT practice to conflict with a regular season Verona Little League (VLL) game, and VLL will work with VBTT coaches to minimize potential conflicts. It is understood that players may have vacations, illness, injuries, family obligations, or other emergencies that will prevent attendance. However, upfront communication about preplanned absences to coaches is important.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Eligibility:</strong></span> VBTT will consist of one or more teams in the 9, 10, 11, 12, 13, and 14 year old age groups. Players are encouraged to try out for their own age group. Players are only allowed to try out for one team. Players must participate in the 2015 regular season VLL season to be eligible for a VBTT.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tryouts:</strong></span> Tryouts for VBTT will be held on <strong>Sunday, September 14</strong> from 12:00-3:00 pm at the VLL Complex.\r\n<div align="center"><strong>12:00 pm - 10U</strong>\r\n<strong>12:45 pm - 11U</strong>\r\n<strong>1:30 pm - 12U</strong>\r\n<strong>2:15 pm - 13U &amp; 14U</strong></div>\r\n<em>Note: Tryouts for the 9U team will be held in the spring.\r\n</em>\r\nA second opportunity will be offered the evening of Wednesday, September 17 (time TBD), but we encourage all to try and make the primary date. Tryouts are mandatory. Participation in tryouts demonstrates commitment and attitude, factors that will be part of the selection process.\r\n\r\nTryouts will consist of stations where players will field and throw ground balls; field and throw fly balls; pitch; and hit. Evaluators will be chosen by the VBTT Committee. The VBTT Committee will also solicit the input of VLL regular season coaches that return player evaluation forms, which will be considered in the formation of each VBTT.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Team Composition:</strong></span> We aim to have at least one team per age group with a minimum of 10 players per team. A coach has the discretion to keep as many players on the roster as he sees fit. If there are enough players to form additional teams, an effort will be made to find a team for every player that participates in the tryout process--provided that there are enough qualified coaches to support multiple teams. If there are enough players and qualified coaches to support multiple teams per age group, the coaches will work with the VBTT Committee to divide the teams as they see fit. This does not necessarily mean an "A" and "B" team, as player/coach availability may play a role in team composition.\r\n\r\nIf there are not enough players to form two teams (less than 10), a coach may choose to carry additional players for specific tournaments.  Due to preplanned absences or emergencies this will allow more players to have an opportunity to participate on a VBTT. This is one reason why upfront communication about preplanned absences is crucial to help determine roster size for a team. If a player can only commit to 50% of the tournaments a coach may still choose to keep that player on the team and increase the number of players carried on the roster. Only those players that participated in the VBTT tryouts will be eligible to be added to a roster during the season.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Coach Selection:</strong></span> The VBTT Committee will decide on team coaches. VBTT will select coaches based on the composition of the team, interest expressed by VLL coaches, and judgment of the VBTT and VLL Board Members.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Team Schedule:</strong></span> Each VBTT coach has the autonomy to set their own practice and tournament schedule. Each VBTT will play in 4-9 tournaments each season. Anything more or less than this will need authorization from the VBTT Committee. Teams are encouraged to host tournaments, three-team events, or double headers at the Verona Little League Complex in order to minimize travel and expense. <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Parents of VBTT players are expected to volunteer at events their team hosts.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Cost to Participate:</strong></span> In addition to the time commitment, there will be fees to offset team practices in the indoor facility, uniforms, and tournament fees. Cost to participate will vary on the number of tournaments a team enters but have ranged from $150-$200 for past summer tournament teams. If your player is invited to participate in the Verona Baseball School, it will also have an additional, nominal fee. If needed and requested, financial assistance is available subject to VBTT Committee review.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Player Self-nomination:</strong></span> In addition to basic personal data, your player will also need to respond to these questions on the form:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Dates you expect to be unavailable for the tryout, practices, or games through August 2015. We realize this may change throughout the year, but information now will help coaches develop their roster early.</li>\r\n	<li>Your strongest positions.</li>\r\n	<li>Brief description of why you feel you should be selected and what you can bring to the team.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p align="center"><span style="font-size: large;"><strong><a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1_Vn_R7f7JsXTf00l-zsy_QSSCB3s3heY2CNvzCH-k3U/viewform?usp=send_form" rel="nofollow">Follow this link to fill out the self-nomination form.</a></strong></span></p>\r\n<span style="color: #ff0000;">Self-nomination forms should be submitted no later than\r\n11:59 pm on Friday, 9/12/2014.</span>\r\n\r\n<br clear="all" /> <a name="news5763177"></a> <span style="font-family: Arial;"><b>Thursday, June 19</b></span>\r\n<a href="http://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/news/index.cfm?id=5763177&amp;cat=368795"><span id="title"><b>2014 Tournament Teams</b></span></a>\r\n<br clear="all" /> <a name="news5770226"></a> <span style="font-family: Arial;"><b>Friday, June 27</b></span>\r\n<a href="http://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/news/index.cfm?id=5770226&amp;cat=368795"><span id="title"><b>2014 Tournament Team Calendar</b></span></a>', 'Tournament Teams', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tournament-teams', '', '', '2014-12-05 04:03:46', '2014-12-05 04:03:46', '', 18, 'http://localhost/AdvancedPHP/veronalittleleague/?page_id=24', 3, 'page', '', 0),
