(179, 1, '2014-12-05 03:17:40', '2014-12-05 03:17:40', 'With regular season games completed, all seeds have been set for the tournament. Brackets, game schedules, and results can be found in the <a href="http://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/news/index.cfm?cat=368785">End-of-Season Tourney tab</a> to the left.\r\n\r\nCoaches, the Tournament Rules document that was e-mailed to you can also be found in the <a href="http://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/handouts/index.cfm?cat=176875&amp;id=933919">Handout - Rules section</a>.\r\n<strong>Handout:</strong> <a href="http://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/handouts/index.cfm?cat=227089&amp;id=1007633">Registration, Parent Forms, &amp; Coaching Application</a>', 'End-of-Season Tournament ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '107-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-05 03:17:40', '2014-12-05 03:17:40', '', 107, 'http://localhost/AdvancedPHP/veronalittleleague/107-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(180, 1, '2014-12-05 03:26:57', '2014-12-05 03:26:57', '<h2>Rules</h2>\r\nRules for 2014 can be found through the handouts link below. Remember this helpful change from last year: pitchers may finish an at-bat to the current batter when crossing a days-of-rest or pitch limit threshold. They then observe rest required for the threshold crossed in that final batter, not the total pitch count. See the rules for the exact details of this change.\r\n\r\nIn addition, here is a document that describes the Little League pitch count rule along with a log for keeping track of pitching during a game.\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.eteamz.com/z/admin/images/file_pdf.gif" alt="Pitching Guide" width="20" height="16" border="0" /> <a href="http://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/files/Pitchingguide.pdf" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Pitching Guide</a>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.eteamz.com/z/admin/images/file_pdf.gif" alt="Pitch Count Log" width="20" height="16" border="0" /> <a href="http://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/files/Pitching_Log_1.pdf" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Pitch Count Log</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Handout:</strong> <a href="http://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/handouts/index.cfm?cat=176875&amp;id=933919">Rules</a>\r\n<h2>Safety &amp; Injury Prevention</h2>\r\nAll players must submit a <a href="https://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/files/2014Medical_Release_Form.pdf">Medical Release Form</a> (<a href="https://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/files/2014Es_Medical_Release_Form.pdf">Spanish</a>) to you. Please keep them with your coaching gear so you have them whenever you are practicing or playing a game in case of an emergency.\r\n\r\nOther useful safety information is in the handouts link below including important information for you and your players'' parents about identifying and dealing with concussions. You should also visit the CDC''s <a href="http://www.cdc.gov/concussion/HeadsUp/youth.html" rel="nofollow">Heads Up</a> campaign to increase awareness, diagnosing, and prevetion of head injuries. All players and parents need to read, sign, and return the <a href="https://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/files/ConcussionAcknowledgementform.pdf">Concussion Acknowledgement Form</a>, which you or your team parent should collect and turn into the league. There is a <a href="http://www.nfhslearn.com/electiveDetail.aspx?courseID=38000" rel="nofollow">free on-line course</a> offered by the National Federation of High Schools (NFHS) where you can learn quite a bit more about the impact of concussions, how to identify them, and how to manage them.\r\n\r\nArm injuries are becoming more prevelent due to a combination of poor throwing mechanics and overuse. Adhering to the Little League mandated pitch counts and days of rest is a good start. Learning how to coach better technique will also help our players stay healthy. We have had two talks in recent years from members of the UW Health Sports Medicine staff. These are available below, along with some video demos of useful practice drills to promote proper warm-up and reinforce better throwing mechanics.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Karl Fry 2012 - <a href="https://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/files/KarlFryInjuryTalk2012.pdf">Important Concepts for Youth Baseball Coaches</a></li>\r\n	<li>Marc Sherry 2014 - <a href="https://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/files/DevelopingHealthyPitchers_Sherry_final.pdf">Developing Healthy Young Pitchers</a>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Performance Enhancement Drills - [<a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BxVp-E8tSqV1WlVLNzN6cllTS3c/edit?usp=sharing" rel="nofollow">MOV</a>] - [<a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BxVp-E8tSqV1Q1oxcDhsMlhtTjA/edit?usp=sharing" rel="nofollow">WMV</a>]</li>\r\n	<li>Mechanical Enhancement Drills - [<a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BxVp-E8tSqV1ajMzNWRKYk1vTVE/edit?usp=sharing" rel="nofollow">MOV</a>] - [<a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BxVp-E8tSqV1RHRUUlFYS25YbVU/edit?usp=sharing" rel="nofollow">WMV</a>]</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Handout:</strong> <a href="http://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/handouts/index.cfm?cat=176875&amp;id=935549">Safety &amp; Injury Prevention</a>\r\n<h2>Practice &amp; Drill Ideas</h2>\r\nCheck out the handouts link below for a <a href="https://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/files/CoachesClinicHandout.PDF">comprehensive coaching guide</a> from Coach Brad D''Orazio that complements his clinics. There are league-specific coaching tips, drills, and practice plans included as well.\r\n\r\nPractice sheets (in the handouts link below) and videos are courtesy Coach D''Orazio. Videos may take a minute to load depending on your connection speed.\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.eteamz.com/z/admin/images/file_mov.gif" alt="" width="20" height="16" /> <a href="http://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/videos/VID00051.mov">Proper baseball throwing grip</a>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.eteamz.com/z/admin/images/file_mov.gif" alt="" width="20" height="16" /> <a href="http://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/videos/VID00048.mov">Intro to throwing</a>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.eteamz.com/z/admin/images/file_mov.gif" alt="" width="20" height="16" /> <a href="http://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/videos/VID00049.mov">Intro to the swing</a>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.eteamz.com/z/admin/images/file_mov.gif" alt="" width="20" height="16" /> <a href="http://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/videos/VID00050.mov">Soft toss</a>\r\n\r\nSome other sites with useful youth baseball instruction and drills:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.littleleaguecoach.org/" rel="nofollow">Little League International Coach Resource Center</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.baseball-tutorials.com/" rel="nofollow">Baseball Drills &amp; Coaching Tips</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.qcbaseball.com/drills/baseball_drills1.aspx" rel="nofollow">Quality Coaching Baseball</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Handout:</strong> <a href="http://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/handouts/index.cfm?cat=176875&amp;id=936470">Practice &amp; Drills</a>\r\n<h2>Software aids</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.lineupmanager.net/index.htm" rel="nofollow">LineUp Manager</a>: An Excel workbook with macros that can help coaches plan lineups, field positions, and stats. Keeps track of season-long position, batting, and hitting stats. Free trial lets you track a few games.</li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.gamechanger.io/" rel="nofollow">GameChanger</a>: iOS in-game scorekeeping app. Game review and stats are kept over a season for your team through their website.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Notes from the Shed</h2>\r\n<img src="http://tbn0.google.com/images?q=tbn:4DI6cBEQfue0tM:http://www.eagleparbirdie.com/50226711/bill%2520murray.jpg" alt="" width="109" height="115" />\r\nKarl asks:\r\n\r\nAre you the home team playing the last game of the day on your field? If so, your team is responsible for "putting the field to bed". Find out how by - <a href="http://www.eteamz.com/VeronaLittleLeague/files/NotesFromTheShed.doc">clicking here</a>.', 'Coaches Corner', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '14-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-05 03:26:57', '2014-12-05 03:26:57', '', 14, 'http://localhost/AdvancedPHP/veronalittleleague/14-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(181, 1, '2014-12-05 03:29:54', '2014-12-05 03:29:54', '<h2>Concessions Shifts</h2>\n<span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>All families must complete 2 hours of concession volunteering per player for the 2014 regular season.</strong></span> More hours will be required for players participating in extended or tournament season. Volunteers must be at least 18 years old.\n\nConcession sales are our largest fundraising effort.<strong> Please make every effort to show up for your assigned shift or find a replacement</strong> (e.g., swap with another family). You can check your shift assignments and make changes through our VolunteerSpot link:\n\n<a href="http://vols.pt/6CJJrB" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://www.volunteerspot.com/images/signup.gif" alt="" border="0" /></a>\n\nIf you have not visited the site this year, it will ask for your e-mail address. Use this same e-mail if you need to change or reschedule a shift (e.g., a night that was rained-out). After you make a reservation, your shift date will be highlighted in green on the calendar. Dates with openings are blue. Click on a date to see the time slot details or to change your assignment.\n\nIf you have any questions about scheduling or problems with the VolunteerSpot, please e-mail<a href="mailto:vllauxilliary@gmail.com" rel="nofollow">vllauxilliary@gmail.com</a>.\n<h2>Meal Deals</h2>\n<table border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2" align="center">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>#1: Hot Dog, Chips &amp; Drink</strong></td>\n<td><strong>$4.00</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>#2: Hamburger, Chips &amp; Drink</strong></td>\n<td><strong>$5.00</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>#3: Cheeseburger, Chips &amp; Drink</strong></td>\n<td><strong>$5.50</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>#4: Brat, Chips &amp; Drink</strong></td>\n<td><strong>$5.00</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>#5: Milio''s Sub, Chips &amp; Drink</strong></td>\n<td><strong>$7.00</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>#6: Milio''s 